cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV) sub-categories, as it deals with domain adaptation in image classification tasks. It also involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and natural language processing (cs.CL) techniques, as it proposes a paradigm for early detection and classification of target samples. Additionally, the use of optimal frameworks for different target samples suggests the involvement of neural networks (cs.NE) in the proposed approach.
